title: Tiffany Faʻaeʻe
text:
Karameli Tiffany Faaee (born November 14, 1982) is an American <a href="rugby%20union">rugby union</a> player. She debuted for the in 2016. She captained the <a href="United%20States%20women%27s%20national%20rugby%20union%20team">US Eagles</a> to the <a href="2017%20Women%27s%20Rugby%20World%20Cup">2017 Women's Rugby World Cup</a> in <a href="Ireland">Ireland</a>. She competed at the 2017 Can-Am Series.
Faaee has represented <a href="Samoa%20women%27s%20national%20rugby%20league%20team">Samoa</a> and <a href="New%20Zealand%20women%27s%20national%20rugby%20league%20team">New Zealand</a> in <a href="rugby%20league">rugby league</a>. She played most of her rugby in New Zealand. She moved to the United States in 2013.
In 2018, Faeaee signed as an assistant coach of <a href="Rugby%20United%20New%20York">Rugby United New York</a>, a <a href="Major%20League%20Rugby">Major League Rugby</a> expansion team.
